#!/usr/bin/env python3
# pylint: disable=invalid-name  # hyphens are required by the git-subcommand convention
"""git-ai-commit — commit staged changes with an AI-generated message.

Analyses the Git index of the current repository and generates a detailed,
informative commit message using a language model, then optionally commits.

This tool automatically gathers context from:
  - Staged changes (diff, with binary and generated files skipped and hunk-aware
    truncation applied)
  - Git status and recent commit history
  - Repository-level guidance: AGENTS.md, AGENT.md, GEMINI.md, CLAUDE.md,
    CONTEXT.md, INSTRUCTIONS.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, HACKING.md,
    ARCHITECTURE.md, and STYLEGUIDE.md.
  - Tool-specific rules: .kilo/agent/, .kilo/command/, .amazonq/rules/,
    .kiro/rules/, .kiro/steering/, .gemini/rules/, .kilocode/, .cursorrules,
    .clinerules, .windsurfrules, and q.rules.
  - User-level guidance: ~/.config/git-ai-commit/instructions.md
  - Git commit template: (from `git config commit.template`)

The kilo backend uses the kilo CLI (`kilo run`) with the `--agent=code` option
and resolves model names by reading the kilo configuration file (~/.config/kilo/kilo.jsonc)
to determine the provider prefix if not provided.

Usage
-----
  git-ai-commit [OPTIONS] [-- GIT-COMMIT-OPTIONS]
  git ai-commit [OPTIONS] [-- GIT-COMMIT-OPTIONS]
  git ai-commit --amend
  echo "context" | git ai-commit --yes
  git ai-commit --yes -- --no-verify --signoff

Options
-------
  --amend              Amend the previous commit, including its message as context
  --context TEXT       Supplemental context/prompt for the AI
   --backend BACKEND    API backend: kilo (default), github-models, copilot,
                        antigravity, agy
     --model   MODEL      Model name (env: GIT_AI_COMMIT_MODEL or GIT_AI_COMMIT_KILO_MODEL;
                         for kilo backend, model is resolved against kilo config
                         ~/.config/kilo/kilo.jsonc to add provider prefix if needed;
                         default: qwen/qwen3-coder-next)
     --api     URL        API base URL override (env: GIT_AI_COMMIT_API)
  --dry-run            Print generated message to stdout; do not commit
  -y/--yes             Commit without interactive confirmation
  -e/--edit            Open generated message in $EDITOR before committing
  --no-instructions    Skip all instruction/context files; use only the diff
  -h/--help            Show this help and exit
  --                   Pass all remaining arguments verbatim to git commit
                       (e.g. --no-verify, --signoff, --gpg-sign=<key>)

Backends
--------
    kilo          LiteLLM-compatible endpoint via kilo CLI (`kilo run --agent=code`).
                  Model names are resolved against the kilo configuration file
                  (~/.config/kilo/kilo.jsonc); if a model name lacks a provider prefix,
                  the prefix is automatically added by looking up the model in the config.
                  The token is read from `GIT_AI_COMMIT_TOKEN` and passed to the kilo CLI
                  via the `KILO_SERVER_PASSWORD` environment variable.
                  The API base URL can be overridden via `GIT_AI_COMMIT_API` (passed to kilo
                  CLI as `KILO_SERVER_URL`) or `--api` option.
                  Note: The `kilo` CLI must be installed and available in PATH.

  github-models GitHub Models inference API (https://models.inference.ai.azure.com).
                Default model: gpt-4o.
                Token: GIT_AI_COMMIT_TOKEN → GITHUB_TOKEN/GH_TOKEN → gh auth token.
                Falls back to the copilot backend on 401/403.

  copilot       GitHub Copilot API (https://api.githubcopilot.com).
                Default model: gpt-4o.
                Token: exchanges a GitHub OAuth token for a short-lived Copilot token.

  antigravity / agy
                Antigravity CLI backend using `agy -p -`.
                If a model is specified via --model (or GIT_AI_COMMIT_MODEL),
                it is passed to `agy` as `--model <model>`. Otherwise,
                `agy` uses its default configured model. No API token or URL
                resolution is required for this backend.

Environment variables
---------------------
    GIT_AI_COMMIT_TOKEN         API token for backends. For kilo backend: passed to
                                kilo CLI via KILO_SERVER_PASSWORD environment variable.
    GIT_AI_COMMIT_MODEL         Default model name
    GIT_AI_COMMIT_API           API base URL; for kilo backend: passed to kilo CLI via
                                KILO_SERVER_URL environment variable
    GIT_AI_COMMIT_BACKEND       Default backend (kilo, github-models, copilot, antigravity, or agy)
    GIT_AI_COMMIT_KILO_API      kilo backend base URL (deprecated; use GIT_AI_COMMIT_API)
    GIT_AI_COMMIT_KILO_MODEL    kilo backend default model (deprecated; use GIT_AI_COMMIT_MODEL)

    KILO_SERVER_URL             API base URL for kilo backend (overrides config)
    KILO_SERVER_PASSWORD        API token for kilo backend (overrides config)

Token resolution (kilo backend):
    1. GIT_AI_COMMIT_TOKEN → KILO_SERVER_PASSWORD (if not set, no token is sent to the API)

Token resolution (github-models / copilot backends):
   1. GIT_AI_COMMIT_TOKEN
   2. GITHUB_TOKEN / GH_TOKEN
   3. `gh auth token`
   4. ~/.config/gh/hosts.yml

Token resolution (github-models / copilot backends):
  1. GIT_AI_COMMIT_TOKEN
  2. GITHUB_TOKEN / GH_TOKEN
  3. `gh auth token`
  4. ~/.config/gh/hosts.yml
"""

